Annotation: Lightning strike in Pacific City led to isolation of both cable lines from shore station equipment, when Power Feed Equipment High Voltage Opening Switches operated. All deployed infrastructure went offline.

Power Feed Equipment failure during major utility power issues related to lightning strike on Pacific City electrical sub-station.  All deployed infrastructure went offline. Power was restored on February 16. No hardware issue subsea was identified.
